# Repository imports: prefer module alias

When a service/router uses a repository, prefer importing the **repository module** and aliasing it as `<name>_repository` (or `<domain>_repository`) instead of importing many functions directly. This keeps call sites explicit, reduces name collisions, and makes refactors safer.

```python
# ❌ BAD — many symbols pulled into local scope
from app.repositories.user_repository import create_user, get_user_by_email

existing = await get_user_by_email(db, email)
user = await create_user(db, user_in)
```

```python
# ✅ GOOD — explicit module alias
import app.repositories.user_repository as user_repository

existing = await user_repository.get_user_by_email(db, email)
user = await user_repository.create_user(db, user_in)
```
